sbml2modelica.abstractmodel.values

Class AbstractFormula

  • java.lang.Object
    • sbml2modelica.abstractmodel.values.AbstractFormula
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<AbstractObject>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractKineticFormula

    public class AbstractFormula
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<AbstractObject>
    An AbstractFormula represents a mathematical formula, expressed in function of variables and functions of an AbstractModel. An AbstractFormula is an Iterable object over a set of AbstractObjects, that represent the variables that appear in the formula.
    Author:
    Maggioli Filippo

    • Constructor Detail

      • AbstractFormula

        public AbstractFormula(AbstractModel model,
                       org.sbml.jsbml.ASTNode formula)
                throws NullAbstractModelException,
                       NullFormulaException
        Constructor initializes the model in which the AbstractFormula is defined with the given AbstractModel and the formula with a deep copy of the given ASTNode. If the given AbstractModel or the given ASTNode are null, then the AbstractFormula is not created and a proper exception is thrown.
        Parameters:
        model - The AbstractModel in which the AbstractFormula is defined
        formula - The ASTNode that represents the formula of the AbstractFormuka.
        Throws:
        NullAbstractModelException - When model == null.
        NullFormulaException - When formula == null.

        protected void generateDependencies(org.sbml.jsbml.ASTNode formula)
        This method generates the dependencies of the given ASTNode. A dependency is an AbstractObject whose the identifier appears as a variable in the formula.
        Parameters:
        formula - The formula whose the dependencies must be computed.
